Rating: 4
This served many more than eight, so it wasn't as pricey as mentioned in other reviews. I found it best to unmold ahead of time and "clean up" the edges with a sharp knife (chef's treats) instead of using a warm spatula to smooth the sides, as suggested, because that blurred the ice cream layers. It made a great presentation for a casual italian-american dinner party.

Rating: 4
Made this in a bundt mold for a wedding reception. To remove from mold just dip in a pan of boiling water for 10 seconds and repeat until loose enough to reverse onto a plate. This cake was outstanding - both visually and taste-wise. Was prettier than the wedding cake!

Rating: 4
This is a great recipe to make with an electrical ice cream maker. The icecreams come out at just the right level of softness. I soaked the cherries in Gran Marnier overnight, dried them off, then added them to the icecream when it was done.

